s 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Devon and Cornwall, of Norman origin): variant of   Cundy  . Compare   Candee  .","French (southern): unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Cundy","meanings":["English (Cornwall and Devon, of Norman origin): habitational name from any of several places in Normandy and Picardy called Condé, a French form of the Gaulish <i>condate</i> ‘junction of rivers’. Members of the de Condé family held land in Lincolnshire, Kent, Leicestershire, Cambridgeshire, and Yorkshire in the 12th century. The strong presence of the surname in 16th-century Cornwall and Devon is unexpected, but is probably the result of migration from counties further east or north. Derivation from the Cornish language is implausible, and there is no known place in Cornwall which could have given rise to it as a habitational name."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Berthilde De Baillescourt de Conty was born in 1126, in Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, her father, Hugues DE BAILLESCOURT, was 48 and her mother, Yolande DE LANDAS-VAN HUSSCHE, was 37. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Wauthier De Dainville. She died in 1159, in Dainville, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, at the age of 33."},"et":{"1126–1159":"1126–1159","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1121–1179":"1121–1179","1152–1197":"1152–1197","1187–1221":"1187–1221","1078–1141":"1078–1141","1089–1138":"1089–1138","1187":"1187","1121":"1121","1165":"1165","1197":"1197","1141":"1141","1152":"1152","1138":"1138","1116":"1116","1126":"1126","1159":"1159","1179":"1179","1089":"1089","1078":"1078","1221":"1221","Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Baillescourt (Puisieux), Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Dainville, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Dainville, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1126–1159":"1126–1159","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1121–1179":"1121–1179","1152–1197":"1152–1197","1